* $3 – the title of the revision

aef3edd43ae2088a:
Exception message thrown when a codepoint exceeds the inclusive range U+0000 to U+10FFFF having an assigned value in the Unicode/ISO/IEC 10646 standards: in such case, that codepoint cannot be encoded to UTF-8 as a sequence of 1 to 4 bytes.

This does not require the codepoint to be used as a valid character in plain text, so it still allows the encoding of any non-character or surrogate (so its encoding into a string is not necessarily checked to form a valid UTF-8 text), it also does not check if the codepoint is reserved or assigned to a character, and texts containing that codepoint are not required to be in a normalized form.
